===Noun===
'''arcology'''
# Urban development theory proposed by Paolo Soleri involving three-dimensional building methods and efficient use of space, resources.  Stems from ARChitechture + ecOLOGY.  Concepts from both fields are integrated to form a radical new living environment.  Arcology is the opposite of [[Urban Sprawl]].
# A structure built according to the principles of arcology.  Intended characteristics include internal greenspace, extensive mass transit and minimal use of automobile, maximum dependence upon renewable energy sources, building "upward" as opposed to "outward."  Somewhat similar to the "domed city" concept prevalent in [[sci-fi]].